()1️⃣ AttributeDefinition ka matlab?
AttributeDefinition basically identity ya object ke ek property ka blueprint hai.
agar kisi Identity (user) ka firstName, lastName, email, employeeId hai, toh in sab ke liye metadata / rules AttributeDefinition me store hote hain.
Ye define karta hai:
Attribute ka type (String, Integer, Boolean, Date)
Attribute ka format (agar koi format restriction hai, jaise date format)
Attribute ki length ya size limit
Attribute ka visibility aur editability
Attribute ka default value.

2️⃣ AttributeDefinition ke andar kya hota hai (properties / methods):-
()getPopulation() / setPopulation(Filter population):--------------Agar ye attribute filtered population ke liye hai (optional)
getName() / setName(String name):-------------------------------------Attribute ka naam (jaise firstName)
getType() / setType(Class type):--------------------------------------Data type (String, Integer, Date)
getFormat() / setFormat(String format):-------------------------------Format rules, jaise date ka yyyy-MM-dd
isRequired() / setRequired(boolean):-------------------------------------Ye attribute mandatory hai ya nahi
isReadOnly() / setReadOnly(boolean):-----------------------------------User edit kar sakta hai ya nahi
isHidden() / setHidden(boolean):---------------------------------------UI me attribute dikhega ya hidden hoga
getDefaultValue() / setDefaultValue(Object):---------------------------Default value agar user ne nahi di
getOrder() / setOrder(int):--------------------------------------------UI me display order
getWidth() / setWidth(int):-----------------------------------------------UI me width
getLabel() / setLabel(String):----------------------------------------Friendly label jo UI me dikhe

3️⃣ AttributeDefinition ka kaam:-
()Validation:-
Ye define karta hai ki attribute ka data valid hai ya nahi.
Example: Email attribute me format xyz@domain.com hona chahiye.

()UI Control:-
Ye decide karta hai ki attribute UI me dikhega, editable hoga ya hidden hoga.

()Default Values & Required Rules:-
Agar user value nahi deta toh default value set karega.
Agar required hai aur value nahi hai, toh error throw karega.

()Integration / Provisioning:
Jab ye attribute kisi application ya system ke sath sync hota hai,
Toh AttributeDefinition ke rules ke according hi data pass hota hai.

4️⃣ DB me kya save hota hai?
--1️⃣ AttributeDefinition DB me
DB me jo AttributeDefinition table me store hota hai (Table: spt_attribute/spt_attributedefinition):-
Sirf metadata / rules / key store hoti hai.
Example: name = firstName, type = String, required = true, defaultValue = Unknown
Matlab ye table sirf batata hai ki attribute ka structure kaisa hai.
Isme actual user ki value nahi hoti.

2️⃣ User ki value kahan store hoti hai?
Actual value identity object ke table me store hoti hai, jaise: spt_identity/spt_identity_attribute table.
Example:-
identityId	attributeName	        value
101	         firstName	            John
101	         lastName	            Singh
102	         firstName	            Priya
Matlab: DB me key-value pair ke form me identity-specific value store hoti hai,
aur metadata (AttributeDefinition) alag table me hota hai.

()methods list:-
getName()
setName(String name)
getType()
setType(Class type)
getFormat()
setFormat(String format)
isRequired()
setRequired(boolean required)
isReadOnly()
setReadOnly(boolean readOnly)
isHidden()
setHidden(boolean hidden)
getDefaultValue()
setDefaultValue(Object value)
getOrder()
setOrder(int order)
getWidth()
setWidth(int width)
getLabel()
setLabel(String label)
getPopulation()
setPopulation(Filter population)
equals(Object obj)
hashCode()
toString()
clone()
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
1️⃣ Setup Example:-
AttributeDefinition attr = new AttributeDefinition();
attr.setName("firstName");
attr.setType(String.class);
attr.setFormat("text");
attr.setRequired(true);
attr.setReadOnly(false);
attr.setHidden(false);
attr.setDefaultValue("Unknown");
attr.setOrder(1);
attr.setWidth(100);
attr.setLabel("First Name");

2️⃣ Methods with Description & Output:-

1. getName() / setName(String name):-
Description: Attribute ka naam get/set karta hai.
System.out.println(attr.getName());  // Output: firstName
attr.setName("lastName");
System.out.println(attr.getName());  // Output: lastName

2. getType() / setType(Class type):-
Description: Attribute ka data type set/get karta hai.
System.out.println(attr.getType());  // Output: class java.lang.String
attr.setType(Integer.class);
System.out.println(attr.getType());  // Output: class java.lang.Integer

3. getFormat() / setFormat(String format):-
Description: Attribute ke liye format rules set/get karta hai (jaise text, email, date).
System.out.println(attr.getFormat());  // Output: text
attr.setFormat("email");
System.out.println(attr.getFormat());  // Output: email

4. isRequired() / setRequired(boolean required):-
Description: Attribute mandatory hai ya optional ye check karta hai.
System.out.println(attr.isRequired());  // Output: true
attr.setRequired(false);
System.out.println(attr.isRequired());  // Output: false

5. isReadOnly() / setReadOnly(boolean readOnly):-
Description: Attribute editable hai ya read-only ye check karta hai.
System.out.println(attr.isReadOnly());  // Output: false
attr.setReadOnly(true);
System.out.println(attr.isReadOnly());  // Output: true

6. isHidden() / setHidden(boolean hidden):-
Description: UI me attribute visible hai ya hidden ye check karta hai.
System.out.println(attr.isHidden());  // Output: false
attr.setHidden(true);
System.out.println(attr.isHidden());  // Output: true

7. getDefaultValue() / setDefaultValue(Object value):-
Description: Agar user value nahi deta, toh default value set/get karta hai.
System.out.println(attr.getDefaultValue());  // Output: Unknown
attr.setDefaultValue("N/A");
System.out.println(attr.getDefaultValue());  // Output: N/A

8. getOrder() / setOrder(int order):-
Description: UI me attribute ka display order set/get karta hai.
System.out.println(attr.getOrder());  // Output: 1
attr.setOrder(2);
System.out.println(attr.getOrder());  // Output: 2

9. getWidth() / setWidth(int width):-
Description: UI me attribute ka width set/get karta hai.
System.out.println(attr.getWidth());  // Output: 100
attr.setWidth(200);
System.out.println(attr.getWidth());  // Output: 200

10. getLabel() / setLabel(String label):-
Description: UI me user-friendly label set/get karta hai.
System.out.println(attr.getLabel());  // Output: First Name
attr.setLabel("Last Name");
System.out.println(attr.getLabel());  // Output: Last Name

11. getPopulation() / setPopulation(Filter population):-
Description: Filter population ke liye attribute assign/set karta hai.
Filter filter = new Filter("active=true");
attr.setPopulation(filter);
System.out.println(attr.getPopulation());  // Output: Filter object with condition active=true

12. equals(Object obj):-
Description: Check karta hai ki do AttributeDefinition objects same hain ya nahi.
AttributeDefinition attr2 = new AttributeDefinition();
attr2.setName("lastName");
System.out.println(attr.equals(attr2));  // Output: false
attr2.setName("lastName");
System.out.println(attr.equals(attr2));  // Output: true (agar equals override properly hua hai)

13. hashCode():-
Description: Object ka unique integer representation return karta hai.
System.out.println(attr.hashCode());  // Output: ek integer jaise 12345678

14. toString():-
Description: Object ka string representation return karta hai.
System.out.println(attr.toString());  
// Output example: AttributeDefinition{name='lastName', type=class java.lang.Integer, required=false, ...}

15. clone():-
Description: Object ka exact copy banata hai.
AttributeDefinition attrClone = attr.clone();
System.out.println(attrClone.getName());  // Output: lastName
System.out.println(attrClone.equals(attr)); // Output: true (agar values same hain)
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
